# Loading & tuning Redshift

## Getting data in

- **`COPY`** — parallel bulk load from S3 (CSV/JSON/Parquet…), ≫ faster than `INSERT`. Pattern: **land in S3 → COPY**
- **Spectrum** — query S3 **directly** via external tables (Glue Catalog), join to in-cluster; per-TB scanned

**Split:** hot / joined data **in** Redshift · cold history **in S3** via Spectrum.

## Distribution style (rows across nodes)

- **AUTO** (default) · **KEY** (co-locate join column) · **ALL** (small dims) · **EVEN** (no join key)
- Pattern: fact **KEY** on `customer_id` + dim **ALL** → **local joins, no shuffle**

## Sort keys

Storage order within a node + **zone maps** (min/max) → filters **skip blocks**. Huge for range / time-series.
